txt.en: 'Oh I thought I'd never get my supplies back! Many thanks to you.\n\n'Now I can continue with my trade.'

'No one told me about the bogs. I came here to sell honest goods in exchange for honest money, but since those creatures attacked my waggon, I don't have any goods to sell!

'I'm going to take a massive loss if I can't unload this product here. Could you possibly help me retrieve my items? I am sure those creatures are keeping them. They didn't much care if I ran away and seemed to only want what was in the waggon.

'Coincidentally, I only care about what was in the waggon as well....'
You seem to have collected all of the supplies that the bog-lurkers lifted from Kiria. You should return to Kiria.\n\nKiria can be found in Mâr Naphra.
Kiria asked you to retrieve any stolen goods to which the bog-lurkers may have taken a liking.\n\nThey can be found at Basha Ghând to the north-west.
Kiria's goods were lost during a recent attack from bog-lurkers.
